time required: 40 minutes
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and halve @carrots{6%ounce} lengthwise; cut into ½-inch-thick half-moons. Halve, peel, and finely dice @yellow onion{1}(peeled and finely diced). Peel and mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}(minced).

Lightly coat an #8-by-8-inch baking dish{} with @nonstick cooking spray{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a large, preferably nonstick, pan over medium-high heat. Add carrots and onion; cook, stirring occasionally, until onion is lightly browned and veggies are tender, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Add @ground beef{10%ounce}; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> TIP: Use paper towels to carefully absorb and remove any excess grease.

Stir @BBQ sauce{4%tablespoon}, @ketchup{1%unit}, and ¼ cup water (1⁄3 cup for 4 servings) into pan with beef and veggies. Cook, stirring, until slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Transfer beef filling to prepared #baking dish{}; sprinkle evenly with @cheddar cheese{1/2%cup}.

Unroll @Pillsbury™ Original Crescent Rolls{4%ounce} on a floured work surface.

Pinch seams closed and use a #rolling pin{} (flouring first) to roll out just big enough to cover the inside of your baking dish.

Place dough on top of filling in baking dish.

In a small #microwave-safe bowl{}, combine @garlic{} and @butter{1%tablespoon}(melted). Microwave until melted, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Brush garlic butter over dough. Sprinkle with a pinch of @salt{pinch}.

Bake pot pie on top rack until crust is golden brown, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Let pot pie cool for ~{5%minutes} before serving.

Serve family style directly from baking dish.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.